<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870324-0074 </DOCNO><HL> Textron Units ReceiveAir Force, Army JobsTotaling $65.7 Million</HL><DD> 03/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TXT AN DIA SUN TGTDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Units of Textron Inc. won contracts totaling $65.7 million for high-power laser development for the Air Force and helicopter production for the Army.    The Defense Logistics Agency awarded jet-fuel contracts of $62.1 million to Amoco Oil Co.; $34 million to Diamond Shamrock Refining andamp; Marketing Co., a unit of Diamond Shamrock Corp.; and $31.6 million to Sun Refining andamp; Marketing Co., a unit of Sun Co.    Newport News Shipbuilding andamp; Dry Dock Co., a unit of Tenneco Inc., received a $28.5 million Navy contract for construction services for attack submarines. </TEXT></DOC>